answerText: The Wild Swans at Coole [10] "The Wild Swans at Coole" is by this Irish poet, who wrote another poem about a rough beast, moving its slow thighs, slouching towards Bethlehem to be born.

subject: Literature
question: Question: The title creatures "scatter wheeling in great broken rings / Upon their clamorous wings." For 10 points each: [10] Name this poem whose speaker wanders through the woods, heading to the water, and wonders what will happen "when I awake some day / to find they have flown away?"
